      • getQualifiedAttributeName

        public java.lang.String getQualifiedAttributeName​(java.lang.String attributeName)
        Description copied from interface: HttpSecurityActionContext

        Qualifies the attribute name to this HttpSecurity instance.

        Multiple HttpSecuritySource instances may be registered for the application. Potentially, some even of the same implementation - likely just configured differently for different needs.

        Therefore, may use this method to provide a namespace on the attribute to keep its value isolated to just this instance use of the HttpSecurity.

        Specified by:
        getQualifiedAttributeName in interface HttpSecurityActionContext
        Parameters:
        attributeName - Name of the attribute.
        Returns:
        Qualified attribute name to the HttpSecurity instance.
